# Desktop session stack — Plasma Mobile, all from Arch Linux ARM (aarch64).
# Plasma Mobile runs on its own compositor (kwin_wayland); NOT hosted in Sway.
#
# build-image.sh installs this list into the rootfs (Phase 4). The pocknix-desktop package ships
# only the launcher/switch scripts — it does NOT depend() on this stack, to keep makepkg from
# dragging the whole KDE/Qt tree into the build chroot (see packages/pocknix-desktop/PKGBUILD).

plasma-mobile        # mobile shell + the startplasmamobile session entrypoint
plasma-workspace     # startplasma-wayland + plasmashell (the shell host)
kwin                 # the Wayland compositor Plasma Mobile runs on
plasma-nano          # minimal shell container the mobile shell builds on
plasma-nm            # Wi-Fi / network applet (touch UI)
powerdevil           # power / brightness / suspend management
plasma-settings      # mobile settings app
kscreen              # kscreen-doctor -> the panel rotation/scale transform (rotated-DSI crux)
xdg-user-dirs        # ~/Documents,Pictures,Videos,… integration (Dolphin Places, file dialogs)

# On-screen keyboard: provided by plasma-mobile itself (the `plasma-keyboard` component) and works
# out of the box — pops up when a text field is focused. No standalone maliit-keyboard needed (it's
# AUR-only anyway).

# --- desktop apps ---
# Plasma Mobile ships only the shell; it does NOT pull a terminal/editor/file-manager. Add the
# standard KDE apps the user expects. (These are desktop apps but run fine touch/mobile.)
konsole              # terminal emulator
kate                 # advanced text editor — ALSO provides /usr/bin/kwrite (no standalone kwrite pkg)
dolphin              # KDE file manager
kcalc                # calculator
ark                  # archive manager
gwenview             # image viewer
okular               # document / PDF viewer

# --- browsers ---
firefox              # Firefox
angelfish            # Plasma Mobile's touch-first web browser

# --- Plasma Mobile gear (touch-first apps) ---
koko                 # image gallery
kclock               # clock / alarms / timers
kweather             # weather

# --- Android apps (Waydroid) ---
# Plasma Mobile ships the "Waydroid support" settings KCM but NOT the daemon. waydroid is in Arch
# extra/ALARM (pulls lxc, python-gbinder, nftables, dnsmasq…). Needs the kernel's binder+binderfs
# (added in build-kernel.sh). First run still needs `waydroid init` (downloads the Android image).
waydroid

# --- app store (Flatpak) ---
# Discover is the native KDE store and ships a Flatpak backend; flatpak provides the runtime.
# Flathub is added by pocknix-flathub.service (pocknix-desktop) on first online boot. A GTK store
# like Bazaar is NOT in Arch repos — install it AS a flatpak from Flathub once this is up.
flatpak              # the Flatpak runtime + CLI
discover             # plasma-discover — KDE app store with the Flatpak backend

# --- Bluetooth (KDE UI) ---
bluedevil            # Plasma Bluetooth applet/KCM (talks to bluez)

# --- Pocknix Installer (install-to-internal GUI) ---
# pocknix-installer-gui (overlay) is a kdialog front-end for pocknix-install/uninstall-internal,
# launched from the "Pocknix Installer" app entry. kdialog's deps are all in the Plasma stack above.
kdialog              # the dialogs (confirm / size picker / busy bar)
qt6-tools            # qdbus6 — drives the kdialog progress dialog (indeterminate + close). Already
                     #   on the image transitively (qdbusviewer6 is hidden via the overlay); explicit
                     #   because the installer GUI depends on it.
